The Buhari Diaspora Support Organisation (BDSO) has said that President Muhammadu Buhari and the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) has restored the hope and confidence of Nigerian friends abroad through the consistent fight against corruption. Chairman/Global Cordinator of the group, Mr. Charles Sylvester, in a chat with our correspondent, said: “President Muhammadu Buhari has, no doubt, restored the fading hopes of many Nigerians who were subjected to institutional corruption, looting of our common wealth and impoverishment in the past three years of this government.” He said that a lot of effort had been made to create an enabling environment for the socio-economic and political development of Nigeria through the restoration of values and confidence in the citizenry that there will be light at the end of the tunnel. “Some of the achievements of the Buhari government includes infrastructural development, agricultural revolution, the Treasury single account TSA/BVN Implementation, school feeding programme, loans to traders, improved power supply and many others. “It is in recognition of this advancement by the Buhari/Osinbajo government that the Buhari Diaspora Organization is calling on all Nigerians to support and vote President Muhammadu Buhari for continuity and stability of our great country”, he added. Buhari’s health: Falsehood elevated to an art 2019:  Nigerians in Diaspora affirm support for Buhari’s re-election. ‘Youths need more attention in Buhari’s govt’